# Ontario Readiness Sync (mandatory)

When you change **any** of: Ontario features, readiness scores, phase status, provincial desks, or pages linked from `/ontario-readiness` or `/investor-letter` — update **every** companion in the same session before finishing.

## Canonical source

**`/ontario-readiness`** (`ontario-readiness.html`) is the score and phase truth. Written companion: `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-READINESS-REPORT.md`.

## Companion set (all must match)

| Live page | Written companion |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `/ontario-readiness` | `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-READINESS-REPORT.md` |
| `/investor-letter` | `docs/investor/INVESTOR-LETTER-2026-06.md` |
| `/capabilities` | `docs/MEDIFORGE-CAPABILITIES-GUIDE.md` |
| `/evidence-binder` | `docs/PHASE-*-COMPLETION.md` rows it cites |
| `/ontario-self-assessment` | `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-SPEC-TRACEABILITY.md` |
| Scores/gaps | `docs/ONTARIOMD-GAP-REPORT.md`, `docs/ONTARIO-EMR-IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md` |
| Staff workflows | `user-manual.html` ↔ `docs/USER-MANUAL.md` |
| Handover | `AGENT-HANDOVER.md` session log |

Also sync: `docs/MEDIFORGE-AT-A-GLANCE.md`, `docs/ONTARIOMD-READINESS-PLAN.md`, `capabilities.html` compare table rows that cite readiness %.

## Before you finish a session

1. Run `npm run check:ontario-readiness` (blocks stale scores and missing chart-filing mentions).
2. Run full `npm run check` if promoting to production.
3. Update `AGENT-HANDOVER.md` session log + **Last updated**.
4. If overall score changes: edit `CANONICAL` in `scripts/check-ontario-readiness-sync.mjs` to match `ontario-readiness.html`.

## Never

- Ship code that touches provincial/Ontario UI without updating linked HTML pages and their markdown companions.
- Leave `70–80%` (or older bands) as **overall** readiness on any companion when canonical is `72–82%`.
- Update only one page in the set because "it was a small fix."
